In the [[Uralic_mythologies|Finno-Ugric religion]], a '''karsikko''' was a set of markings made on a tree somewhere between a deceased person's home and their burial site, which they believed would prevent the dead individual's spirit from coming back.<ref>{{cite web|last1=The Editors of Encyclopædia Britannica|title=Kalma - Finno-Ugric religion|url=https://www.britannica.com/topic/kalma|website=Encyclopædia Britannica|publisher=Encyclopædia Britannica, Inc|accessdate=11 December 2016}}</ref>

